Class FreqMap

java.lang.Object
main.java.FreqMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Float>>
public class FreqMap
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Float>>
Class representing a FreqMapEntry instance. A FreqMap is a set of entries (instances of FreqMapEntry) containing, for each author and each text, the results of the analysis of a single input file.

    • globalAuthorFrequency

      private void globalAuthorFrequency​(java.lang.String author)
      Generates a global frequency for each author by computing the average values for each field in the frequency map. Substitutes all the entries of an author with a single entry with the same author name and "global" as title.
      Parameters:
      author - the author's name to compute the average of.

    • update

      private void update​(java.lang.String author, java.lang.String title, java.lang.String field, float value)
      Updates the FreqMap instance by adding a new entry to the set. If an entry with the same author and title exists, the field value is updated with the specified value parameter.
      Parameters:
      author - the author's name.
      title - the title of the writing.
      field - the field name to be updated.
      value - the value to be added/overwritten.
